\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0 A Nominal Definition}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As with aesthetic illusion, there are many terms used to describe this faculty. It is not in the remit to discuss them all, merely draw them together in review. Very commonly it is called }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93imagination\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 (a citation?)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93simulation\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 (a citation?)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  or }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93modelling\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 (a citation?)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , or many other things besides. Each of these have both specific and general meanings within different fields, which can muddy our high-level examination of the entirety of the phenomenon. For example, imagination is used in psychology to mean \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93all mental simulation\u8221\'94, as we mean it, as well as precisely to mean the simulation of prior sensory experiences.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Because of this, and to distinguish our transdisciplinary interest, I will be using a nominal definition, a term around which we can talk, and which we can use to stand for our general interest, whether aesthetic or mundane, incited or sourceless, deliberate or accidental, in the human hallucinatory faculty as an object of interest for artists.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The term I have chosen is }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 AUTOCOSMICS}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . This means \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93self-worlds\u8221\'94, which I think captures the internalised, personal nature of mental simulation, as well as their immersiveness, as well as pointing to their atmospheric osmosis; how other mental faculties, and the world outside the self, can affect and influence them, like meteorites scarring the face of a world. The word \u8216\'91cosmos\u8217\'92, as well, to me stands for a system in tension, an interpolation of many moving parts, rather than the rather static }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93imagination\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , which also confines us to the purely visual: though this is important, it is not the only way to \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91imagine\u8217\'92. We could have used the word \u8216\'91simulation\u8217\'92, which I think also preserves these qualities, but again its numerous popular and specific meanings make life difficult for us. Autocosmics, in being new and nominal, does not place any prior judgement or distinction between \u8220\'93high\u8221\'94 and \u8220\'93low\u8221\'94 fantasy, its source or purpose, only the fact of its existence as a phenomenon, its role within the individual, its varying degrees of immersion and its constant systemic evolution within a mind. I must admit to adapting it from another pleasing term, }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 paracosm}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , used (but not coined) extensively by the developmental psychologist Marjorie Taylor }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 to describe the detailed fictional worlds of both children, lunatics and artists. This cross-generational divide is a nice touch, as is the non-judgemental ascription to all human mental activity, which I feel is preserved in my term. }
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This account, then, in referring to \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93autocosmics\u8221\'94 in general, might be accused of being an act of }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93intellectual hubris\u8221\'94  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 (an attempt to theorise everything, and thus nothing); but I am not trying to unite all mental simulation, or provide a grand theory, or link everything together; I merely want to draw attention to its ubiquity, and the different ways that it has been both courted, ignored and modified by different fields, with the concluding goal of looking outside my own disciplinary boundaries at other examples of this loose collection of human abilities.}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
