\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 In plain English, from a combination of the mind and the body.}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The power of the human brain as a computational object, to compute both internally to itself (memory, for example (}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 cite}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 )), and externally to the bodily. It is arguable whether mental simulation can be thought of as }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 ever }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 entirely mental: phenomenologists such as Andy Clark states that much of our cognition is out in the world (}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8221\'94extended cognition\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). Merleau-Ponty talked about \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93the flesh of the world\u8221\'94, and Shapiro traces changes in more recent history from a }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1\cf3 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 comfortably Cartesian view[s] of mind." }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 To }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93the mind incarnate\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (Shapiro).}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 David Deutsch - }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93it is uncontroversial that the human brain has capabilities that are, in some respects, far superior to those of all other known objects in the cosmos.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The processing of that information takes place within our brains: this is an evolutionary impulse. }{\f2\fs24\b1\i1  }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Holland - }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 General abilities based in the brain and shared by all human beings who have normal brains.\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It relies in general on two major components of mankind\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s biology and psychology: the gathering of information and its processing, either in conjunction or merely processing. }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Man\u8230\'85 is\u8230\'85 a receiver and transmitter of information\u8230\'85 transforms the distillate of his world into memories, mental imagery\u8230\'85 an information processor.\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (Weiz p140).  }
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f3\fs24\b0\i1	\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93The ability to interpret is not acquired; it is constitutive of being human.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0    Stanley Fish}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What, at base, we try to do is make sense of this flood of sensory and mental data, constantly churning and changing all the time, which \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 stimulate people to look for causal connections}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 .\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94  As Donald Norman says, \u8220\'93t}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 he human mind is exquisitely tailored to make sense of the world\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8221\'94; we are \u8220\'93explanatory creatures\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 (cite?)}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 who }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93assimilate reality into systems of transformations\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; mental systems that mean manipulating the raw data into internalised sense-made projections. This comes back the idea of accidental/deliberate; though we can deliberately tweak and make sense of certain things in certain ways, often it is accidental and uncontrolled: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 give it the slightest clues and off it goes, providing explanation, rationalisation, understanding\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8221\'94 . }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Very similar to the }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93integrative coherence\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 of aesthetic illusion from Wolf, in which the reader parses the text with their own lives. This is }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93reproductive imagination\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 cite}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ); reproducing (always partially) the data we receive from the world. This is contrasted with \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93constructive imagination\u8221\'94, or is in partnership with it; using the computational power of the brain to take existing concepts and build new ones out of them, or adapt mental constructs of sensory/bodily/worldly data and change them into something else. }
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Indeed, this sense-making leads us to a wider use of the term \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91narrative\u8217\'92; a }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93mode of mental life\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (Oatley)  as a sequence of consistent events which are relatable and trackable, temporal and causal. It is how we explain the past, predict the future, and plot the present in continuum, give meaning to our existence and determine patterns over a long period of time. It has led, arguably, to the modern practices of science; placing what we know into an experimental mental mode, applying that to the outside world, and comparing the two. Science requires creative leaps combined with this inquisitiveness and pattern-matching ability, which has led to most of our most breathtaking advances as a species }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 (who talks about this?)}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 , and have shaped our complex social natures, as well as coordinating the simplest of our higher (and lower) functions. }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Narrative [is] the most important cognitive macro-frame man has developed to make sense of experience in and of time\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 (Wolf).}
