\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls7\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Childs & Fowler -}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1  \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Since I. A. Richards\u8217\'92s Principles of Literary Criticism (1924), critics have usually been wary of detailed explorations into reader psychology: \u8216\'91willing suspension of disbelief\u8217\'92 (Coleridge) is now more often alluded to than investigated.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  - this is not true at all! Massive link between reader-response theory and psychology.}
